---
import PageLayout from '@/components/layout/PageLayout.astro';
import Container from '@/components/layout/Container.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '@/components/seo/Breadcrumbs.astro';
---

<PageLayout
  title="Cancellation Policy - Telluride Ski Hotels"
  description="Cancellation and refund policy for Telluride Ski Hotels bookings. Understand your options and how to modify or cancel your reservation."
>
  <Container class="py-16 lg:py-20">
    <Breadcrumbs items={[
      { label: 'Home', href: '/' },
      { label: 'Cancellation Policy', href: undefined },
    ]} />

    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto mt-8">
      <h1 class="text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-extrabold text-neutral-900 mb-6">Cancellation & Refund Policy</h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-neutral-600 mb-12">Last Updated: November 14, 2025</p>

      <div class="bg-primary-50 border-l-4 border-primary-600 p-6 rounded-r-lg mb-12">
        <p class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Important Note</p>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed">
          Cancellation and refund policies are determined by the individual accommodation provider or activity operator, not by Telluride Ski Hotels. Policies vary by property, rate type, and booking date. Always review the specific cancellation terms for your reservation before booking.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
        <section class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">1. Understanding Cancellation Policies</h2>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            When you book through Telluride Ski Hotels, you enter into a direct contract with the accommodation provider or activity operator. Each provider sets their own cancellation policy, which is clearly displayed during the booking process and included in your confirmation email.
          </p>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed">
            Common cancellation policy types include:
          </p>
          
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3 mt-6">Free Cancellation</h3>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4 space-y-2 text-neutral-700">
            <li>Cancel up to 24-72 hours before check-in for a full refund</li>
            <li>Most common for mid-range and budget accommodations</li>
            <li>Specific deadlines vary by property</li>
            <li>Cancellations after the deadline typically forfeit the first night or full booking</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3 mt-6">Flexible Cancellation</h3>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4 space-y-2 text-neutral-700">
            <li>Cancel up to 7-14 days before check-in for full or partial refund</li>
            <li>May incur a processing fee (typically 10-25% of total)</li>
            <li>Common for luxury properties and peak season bookings</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3 mt-6">Moderate/Strict Cancellation</h3>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4 space-y-2 text-neutral-700">
            <li>Cancel 14-30 days before check-in for partial refund (typically 50%)</li>
            <li>Cancellations within 14 days forfeit full payment</li>
            <li>Common during peak season (Christmas, New Year's, February)</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3 mt-6">Non-Refundable</h3>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4 space-y-2 text-neutral-700">
            <li>No refund for any cancellations</li>
            <li>Typically offers 10-30% discount compared to refundable rates</li>
            <li>Common for advance purchase rates and special promotions</li>
            <li>Best for travelers with confirmed plans</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">2. How to Cancel Your Reservation</h2>
          
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3 mt-6">Option 1: Contact the Property Directly (Fastest)</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            For the quickest resolution:
          </p>
          <ol class="list-decimal pl-6 mb-4 space-y-2 text-neutral-700">
            <li>Locate your booking confirmation email</li>
            <li>Find the property's direct contact information</li>
            <li>Call or email the property with your confirmation number</li>
            <li>Request cancellation and confirm any refund details</li>
            <li>Get written confirmation of the cancellation</li>
          </ol>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3 mt-6">Option 2: Contact Our Support Team</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            We're happy to assist with cancellations:
          </p>
          <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6 border border-neutral-200 mb-4">
            <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-2"><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:hello@tellurideskihotels.com" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700">hello@tellurideskihotels.com</a></p>
            <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-2"><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:tellurideskihotels@gmail.com" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700">tellurideskihotels@gmail.com</a></p>
            <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4"><strong>Hours:</strong> Monday-Friday, 9am-5pm MST</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Include your confirmation number, name, and booking details in your message.</p>
          </div>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3 mt-6">What You'll Need</h3>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4 space-y-2 text-neutral-700">
            <li>Booking confirmation number</li>
            <li>Name on the reservation</li>
            <li>Check-in and check-out dates</li>
            <li>Property name</li>
            <li>Reason for cancellation (optional but helpful)</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">3. Refund Processing</h2>
          
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3 mt-6">Timeline</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            Refunds are processed according to the property's policy:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4 space-y-2 text-neutral-700">
            <li>Refund approval: 1-3 business days after cancellation request</li>
            <li>Processing to your payment method: 5-10 business days after approval</li>
            <li>Total timeline: Typically 7-14 business days from cancellation to refund appearing in your account</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3 mt-6">Refund Method</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            Refunds are issued to the original payment method used for booking:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4 space-y-2 text-neutral-700">
            <li>Credit card refunds appear as a credit on your statement</li>
            <li>Debit card refunds return to your checking/savings account</li>
            <li>Alternative payment methods follow their respective refund processes</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3 mt-6">Partial Refunds</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed">
            Some cancellation policies result in partial refunds. The refunded amount depends on:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4 space-y-2 text-neutral-700">
            <li>How far in advance you cancel</li>
            <li>The property's specific cancellation policy</li>
            <li>Whether you booked a refundable or non-refundable rate</li>
            <li>Any fees or penalties specified in the booking terms</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">4. Modifications & Changes</h2>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            Want to change your dates or room type instead of canceling?
          </p>
          
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3 mt-6">Date Changes</h3>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4 space-y-2 text-neutral-700">
            <li>Contact the property directly to request date changes</li>
            <li>Many properties allow free date changes if requested in advance</li>
            <li>New dates are subject to availability and current rates</li>
            <li>Some properties charge a modification fee</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3 mt-6">Room/Guest Changes</h3>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4 space-y-2 text-neutral-700">
            <li>Minor changes (guest names, special requests) are usually free</li>
            <li>Changing room type or number of guests may require rebooking</li>
            <li>Price differences apply if upgrading or downgrading</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">5. Special Circumstances</h2>
          
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3 mt-6">Weather & Natural Disasters</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            Extreme weather events (blizzards, road closures, avalanches) may qualify for special consideration:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4 space-y-2 text-neutral-700">
            <li>Contact the property immediately if weather affects your travel</li>
            <li>Many properties offer flexibility for documented travel restrictions</li>
            <li>Travel insurance may cover weather-related cancellations</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3 mt-6">Medical Emergencies</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            Medical emergencies may be considered for cancellation policy exceptions:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4 space-y-2 text-neutral-700">
            <li>Contact the property as soon as possible</li>
            <li>Provide documentation if requested</li>
            <li>Travel insurance typically covers medical cancellations</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3 mt-6">Resort Closures</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed">
            If Telluride Ski Resort closes unexpectedly:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4 space-y-2 text-neutral-700">
            <li>Most properties offer flexible cancellation or date changes</li>
            <li>Contact the property to discuss options</li>
            <li>We'll assist in coordinating with properties during resort closures</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">6. Travel Insurance</h2>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            We strongly recommend purchasing travel insurance, especially for:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4 space-y-2 text-neutral-700">
            <li>Non-refundable bookings</li>
            <li>Peak season travel (Christmas, New Year's, February)</li>
            <li>International travelers</li>
            <li>Group bookings or multiple rooms</li>
            <li>Expensive luxury properties</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            Travel insurance can cover:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4 space-y-2 text-neutral-700">
            <li>Trip cancellation for covered reasons (illness, injury, family emergencies)</li>
            <li>Trip interruption if you must leave early</li>
            <li>Travel delays and weather-related issues</li>
            <li>Lost or delayed luggage</li>
            <li>Medical emergencies while traveling</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">7. No-Show Policy</h2>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            If you do not arrive for your reservation and do not cancel in advance:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4 space-y-2 text-neutral-700">
            <li>You will be charged the full booking amount</li>
            <li>No refund is provided for no-shows</li>
            <li>Remaining nights may be automatically canceled</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed">
            Always contact the property if you cannot make your reservation, even if it's past the cancellation deadline. Some properties may offer partial credit or future travel vouchers.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">8. Disputes & Resolution</h2>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            If you have a dispute about a cancellation or refund:
          </p>
          <ol class="list-decimal pl-6 mb-4 space-y-2 text-neutral-700">
            <li>First, contact the property directly to resolve the issue</li>
            <li>If unresolved, contact our support team at <a href="mailto:hello@tellurideskihotels.com" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700">hello@tellurideskihotels.com</a></li>
            <li>Provide all documentation: confirmation emails, cancellation requests, correspondence</li>
            <li>We'll work with the property on your behalf to reach a fair resolution</li>
            <li>For payment disputes, you may also contact your credit card company</li>
          </ol>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">9. Contact Us</h2>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            Need help with a cancellation or have questions about this policy?
          </p>
          <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6 border border-neutral-200">
            <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-2"><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:hello@tellurideskihotels.com" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700">hello@tellurideskihotels.com</a></p>
            <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-2"><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:tellurideskihotels@gmail.com" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700">tellurideskihotels@gmail.com</a></p>
            <p class="text-neutral-700"><strong>Hours:</strong> Monday-Friday, 9am-5pm MST</p>
          </div>
        </section>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-12 p-6 bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-xl">
        <p class="text-sm text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed text-center">
          <strong class="text-neutral-900">Pro Tip:</strong> Always read the specific cancellation policy for your booking before confirming. Screenshot or save the policy details from your confirmation email. If your plans are uncertain, consider refundable rates or travel insurance.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Container>
</PageLayout>

